gate: OPEN
v:4 role:dev x:frontend
task: S88 T1 — Wire inactivity grace before resume biometry prompt
requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
sprint: S88

context: |
  useLocalSettings already defines local_biometry_inactivity_minutes (default 5)
  but useSessionBiometryLock ignores it — every foreground return triggers
  requestBiometricUnlock. Short app switches feel like "constant" re-auth.

steps:
  1. In useSessionBiometryLock visibility handler, read
     values.local_biometry_inactivity_minutes.
  2. Track last successful unlock time (reuse lastActionTimeRef or dedicated ref).
  3. If elapsed < inactivity window → skip prompt, call onBiometryVerified.
  4. If elapsed ≥ window → existing requestBiometricUnlock flow.
  5. Add SettingsField in MainSettingsSection (or Account Security) for
     inactivity minutes: presets 1 / 5 / 15 / 60 (or numeric stepper).
  6. Add i18n keys for label + helper text (ru/en/bg minimum).

out:
  - src/features/security/hooks/useSessionBiometryLock.ts
  - src/screens/settings/components/MainSettingsSection.tsx
  - src/hooks/useLocalSettings.ts
  - locale JSON files (as per project convention)

done:
  - Background < N minutes → no Face ID on return.
  - Background ≥ N minutes → Face ID required (biometry users only).
  - Setting persists across restarts.
  - pnpm tsc --noEmit passes.
